        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-4738",
        "content": "And many a Nymph who wreathes her brows with sedge And sheds the freshening dew, and, lovelier still The pensive Pleasures sweet, Prepare thy shadowy car.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
